<HL>
   Varity Corp. Seeks
   To Join Operations
   Of K-H Corp. Units
</HL>
<DATE>
05/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A12
</SO>
<CO>
   VAT T.KEL
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   TORONTO -- Varity Corp. said it proposed to amalgamate the
operations of Kelsey-Hayes Canada and its Kelsey-Hayes unit
in a transaction valued at about C$36 million.
   Varity said it plans to offer the minority shareholders of
Kelsey-Hayes Canada either C$20 (US$17.01) a share or a yet
to be determined number of Varity common shares for their
holdings in the Canadian unit.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   At last report, minority shareholders own about about 1.8
million shares of Kelsey-Hayes Canada, or about 27.3% of the
total number of shares outstanding.
   A spokesman for Varity said the proposal is "a logical
extension" of Varity's acquisition last year of Detroit-based
K-H Corp., the parent of Kelsey-Hayes Canada.
   Varity said it has retained Gordon Capital Corp. to review
the proposed amalgamation and to provide a fairness opinion
on the value of the Varity shares to be offered in exchange
for Kelsey-Hayes Canada shares.
   The companies said they expect that the amalgamation
couldn't occur before August.
   At least two-thirds of the shareholders of Kelsey-Hayes
Canada would need to approve the amalgamation at a special
meeting. Varity said Kelsey-Hayes Co. would vote its 72.7%
interest in favor of the amalgamation.
   Kelsey-Hayes Canada has formed a committee of independent
directors to review the proposal.
</TEXT>
