   FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Lincoln National Corp., an insurer,
said it will redeem on June 21 the 500 shares of its
short-term auction rate, or Star, Series C preferred stock
and on June 28 the 500 shares of its Star preferred Series D
preferred.
   The redemption price for each series is $100,000 a share,
plus accumulated dividends. The dividends are $926.92 a share
for Series C and $920.11 a share for Series D. All dividends
will stop accruing on the redemption dates.
