<HL>
   Business Brief -- Owens-Illinois Inc.:
   Loss Narrowed in 1st Period
   On 11% Revenue Increase
</HL>
<DATE>
05/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A13
</SO>
<CO>
   OI
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Owens-Illinois Inc., taken private in a leveraged buy-out
in 1987, reported a narrower first-quarter net loss on 11%
higher revenue, sending its publicly traded bonds higher.
   All of the company's major businesses -- glass containers,
plastics and closures, specialized glass and health care --
posted "strong" performances, Owens-Illinois said in a
Securities and Exchange Commission filing.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Toledo, Ohio, company, taken private in 1987 for $3.64
billion by Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co., reported its
deficit shrank to $12.3 million, or 33 cents a share, from
$32.3 million, or 87 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue
rose to $956.3 million from $855.4 million.
   Owens-Illinois's earnings before depreciation,
amortization, interest and tax rose 29% to $192.2 million
from $149.5 million. And interest coverage -- the number of
times these earnings exceed interest expense -- increased to
1.46 from 1.22.
</TEXT>
