INDUSTRIAL EQUIPMENT, MACHINE TOOLS (IND)
</IN>
<LP>
   Westinghouse Electric Corp., Pittsburgh, said it formed a
partnership to develop robotic technology for use in the
nuclear-service and nuclear-waste markets.
   The company said its partners in the venture are Carnegie
Mellon University and RedZone Robotics Inc., both of
Pittsburgh. RedZone, which originated at Carnegie Mellon, is
a privately held robotics designer and fabricator.
</LP>
