<IN>
AUTOMOBILES (AUT)
</IN>
<LP>
   Chrysler Corp. said it plans to spend about $150 million
to expand its Kokomo, Ind., transmission plant to prepare for
assembly of a new electronic four-speed automatic
transmission for the 1993 model year.
   The expenditure is part of $190 million in plant
improvement the No. 3 auto maker announced yesterday.
Chrysler also said it will spend about $28 million for new
equipment at its New Castle, Ind., machining and forge plant,
and about $12 million on new tooling for its Kokomo casting
plant.
