derivative of a relatively new four-speed automatic
transmission currently used on many of its front-wheel drive
cars -- is scheduled to begin in May 1992. Construction for
the transmission plant expansion will begin this month and
end in February 1991. The Highland Park, Mich., auto maker
said it plans to continue building the six other
transmissions it now makes at the Kokomo facility.
