<HL>
   International Brief -- Veba AG:
   West German Firm's Profit
   For 1st Quarter Rose 5.3%
</HL>
<DATE>
05/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<CO>
   G.VEB
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Veba AG, a West German energy and chemical concern, said
in an interim report that first-quarter profit climbed 5.3%
to 237 million marks ($144.2 million) from 225 million marks
a year earlier.
   Sales climbed 10% to 13.15 billion marks from 11.93
billion marks.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Pretax profit climbed 6.3% to 605 million marks from 569
million marks.
   The company said higher volume and prices in its mineral
oil division led to a "considerable" increase in that area.
Oil sales climbed 9.2% to 2.53 billion marks from 2.32
billion marks a year earlier; chemical sales jumped 16% to
2.62 million marks from 2.27 million marks; and electricity
sales increased 4.5% to 2.89 billion marks from 2.76 billion
marks.
   Veba said earnings in its electricity, trading,
transportation and services divisions rose slightly from a
year earlier, but weren't able to equal "the high
year-earlier level" in its oil and chemical division. It
didn't break down first-quarter earnings by division.
</TEXT>
