<HL>
   Turkey's Foreign Trade Gap
</HL>
<DATE>
05/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey's foreign trade deficit widened
to $527 million in February from gaps of $91 million a year
earlier and $504 million in January, the state Statistics
Institute said.
   In February, exports on a value basis fell 1% to $988
million from $997 million in January, and rose 3.7% from $953
million a year earlier. Imports totaled $1.52 billion in
February, up slightly from $1.5 billion a month earlier and
up 45% from $1.04 billion a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the first two months of this year, the trade deficit
widened to $1 billion from $383 million a year earlier.
Exports totaled $1.99 billion, up 15% from $1.72 billion a
year earlier, and imports registered $3.02 billion, up 43%
from $2.12 billion.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
