   Sweden's Industrial Production
</HL>
<DATE>
05/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   STOCKHOLM -- Sweden's industrial production in March fell
0.7% from February and 2% from a year earlier, Statistics
Sweden, the national statistics agency, said.
   The drop followed a 0.2% decline in February and a 1.3%
rise in January.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Industrial production in the first quarter fell 1% from a
year earlier, but the decline was from a record level. The
pulp and steel sectors registered drops in production, while
the paper, chemical and engineering industries reported
continued high production levels.
